			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="884">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>&ldquo;Farmed Out&rdquo; had me nodding my head with a sense of validation and connection: finally someone put my feelings into words with the science and experience to back them up. Despite the gravity of the information being conveyed, the interview was a comfort.</p>

<p>In the same issue Al Neipris&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4464">The Primitive Tongue of a Lesser Species</a>&rdquo; had me blinking watery eyes as I turned the page. As the author&rsquo;s granddaughter stated, &ldquo;The sun is like a lamp, Pappy.&rdquo; And so is <em>The Sun</em> to this appreciative reader.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Kendra Zell<br>Sonoma, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

